generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4420 feet, Mount Hancock is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its rugged and challenging terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Hancock Loop Trail**, a **17.6 mile** route gaining **4396 feet** of elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **South Hancock**, which is just 0.6 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
